<HL>
   MEI to Acquire 3 Beauty Salons
</HL>
<DATE>
08/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MEI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   MINNEAPOLIS -- MEI Diversified Inc. said it agreed
definitively to acquire three companies that operate
professional beauty salons in department stores for $50
million, plus assumption of certain liabilities.
   MEI said it will own 80% of a new company formed to
acquire Glemby Co. of New York; Essanelle Salon Co.; and
Maxim's, both of Minneapolis. The remaining 20% of the new
company will be owned by Minneapolis-based Regis Corp., the
current owner of both Essanelle and Maxim's.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   MEI said the combined companies have annual sales of about
$400 million and will operate more than 2,000 salons in the
U.S. and Canada.
   The acquisition is scheduled to be completed by Friday.
</TEXT>
